body:
@halorgium : Thanks for reporting the issue.

At the end of KafkaApis.handleProducerRequest(), we actually call the following to clear the reference to the data records.

      // if the request is put into the purgatory, it will have a held reference
      // and hence cannot be garbage collected; hence we clear its data here in
      // order to let GC re-claim its memory since it is already appended to log
      produceRequest.clearPartitionRecords()

So, not sure why the callback doesn't pick it up. Perhaps we should make ProduceRequest.partitionRecords volatile? Also, we could try clearing it early after the following statement in KafkaApis.handleProducerRequest()?

    val (existingAndAuthorizedForDescribeTopics, nonExistingOrUnauthorizedForDescribeTopics) = produceRequest.partitionRecords.asScala.partition {
      case (topicPartition, _) => authorize(request.session, Describe, new Resource(auth.Topic, topicPartition.topic)) && metadataCache.contains(topicPartition.topic)
    }
